ontent\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01W2X2CYNYfD89nmym36SoHe\",\"name\":\"Edit\",\"input\":{\"replace_all\":false,\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/.claude/plans/moonlit-meandering-catmull.md\",\"old_string\":\"# Fix: `secrets` not allowed in step `if` expressions\\n\\n## Context\\nSteps 1-3 from the previous plan are already applied. The `gh workflow run` dispatch fails because GitHub Actions doesn't allow `secrets` context in step-level `if` conditions — it's only available in `env`, `with`, and `run` blocks. The three Slack steps (lines 52, 96, 123) use `secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL` in their `if` conditions, causing the validation error.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n**File: `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml`**\\n\\n### 1. Add job-level `env` block\\nAfter `timeout-minutes: 60`, before `steps:`, add:\\n```yaml\\n    env:\\n      SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL: ${{ secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}\\n```\\nThis exposes the secret as a job-level environment variable that `if` conditions can reference.\\n\\n### 2. Replace `secrets` references in step `if` conditions\\n\\n| Line | Old | New |\\n|------|-----|-----|\\n| 52 | `secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` | `env.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` |\\n| 96 | `always() && secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` | `always() && env.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` |\\n| 123 | `always() && secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` | `always() && env.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL != ''` |\\n\\n### 3. Update `webhook:` in Slack action `with` blocks\\nLines 58 and 126 pass `${{ secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}` — update to `${{ env.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}` for consistency (both work, but avoids mixing patterns).\\n\\n## Verification\\n```bash\\ngit push\\ngh workflow run e2e-triage.yml --ref alisha/e2e-triage -f run_id=22772950740\\n```\",\"new_string\":\"# Fix: `claude -p` prompt not received due to variadic `--allowedTools` flag\\n\\n## Context\\nThe \\\"Run triage\\\" step in the e2e-triage workflow fails with:\\n```\\nError: Input must be provided either through stdin or as a prompt argument when using --print\\n```\\n\\n**Root cause:** The `--allowedTools` flag accepts variadic arguments (`<tools...>`). When the prompt string follows it as a positional argument, the CLI parser consumes the prompt as another tool name instead of recognizing it as the positional `prompt` argument. So Claude CLI sees no prompt.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n**File: `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml`** (lines 81-95)\\n\\n### Pipe the prompt via stdin instead of passing as positional arg\\n\\nChange the `run:` block from:\\n```yaml\\nrun: |\\n  ARTIFACT_DIR=\\\"e2e/artifacts/ci-${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}\\\"\\n  claude -p \\\\\\n    --model claude-opus-4-6 \\\\\\n    --allowedTools \\\"Bash(mise run *),Bash(gh *),Bash(git *),Read,Write,Edit,Glob,Grep\\\" \\\\\\n    \\\"You are triaging E2E test failures...\\\"\\n```\\n\\nTo:\\n```yaml\\nrun: |\\n  ARTIFACT_DIR=\\\"e2e/artifacts/ci-${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}\\\"\\n  cat <<PROMPT | claude -p \\\\\\n    --model claude-opus-4-6 \\\\\\n    --allowedTools \\\"Bash(mise run *),Bash(gh *),Bash(git *),Read,Write,Edit,Glob,Grep\\\"\\n  You are triaging E2E test failures from CI run ${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}.\\n  Follow the /e2e-triage skill instructions in .claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md.\\n  You are in CI mode (WORKFLOW_RUN_ID is set). Use the CI mode steps.\\n  Artifact directory: ${ARTIFACT_DIR}\\n  CI run URL: ${WORKFLOW_RUN_URL}\\n  Re-run failing tests using the e2e-isolated.yml workflow via gh workflow run.\\n  Do NOT ask questions — act autonomously.\\n  For flaky fixes: create a PR.\\n  For real bugs: create or comment on GitHub issues.\\n  Print a summary table at the end.\\n  PROMPT\\n```\\n\\nThis pipes the prompt via stdin, which `claude -p` reads when no positional prompt is given. The heredoc also avoids quoting issues with the multi-line string.\\n\\n## Verification\\n```bash\\ngit push\\ngh workflow run e2e-triage.yml --ref alisha/e2e-triage -f run_id=22772950740\\n```\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\